    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine Domini. Anno ab incarnatjone eius millesimo octuagesimo primo,
                        temporibus domni <persName key="#Popes" ref="#people/265"
                            >Gregorii</persName> pape cum sede [a]nno octavo, regnante <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/77">Henrico</persName> quondam Henritj
                        impera[tori]s filio, die viesimo primo mensis novembris, ind(itjo)n(e)
                        quarta, [in <rs key="#Fundi">fun]do</rs>
                        <geogName key="#Fundi"><placeName key="#Fundi"
                            >Salecto</placeName></geogName>. Petivi a vobis in Dei nomine <persName
                            key="#Monks"><name ref="Wido Pomposianus">Wido</name></persName> et
                            <persName key="#Monks"><name ref="Maurizo Pomposianus"
                            >Mauritjus</name></persName> hone[sti <rs key="#Monks">m]onachi</rs>
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterii</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis #Fundi #Petiae #Plebs #Monasteries
                            #Rent_in_money #Penalty"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1460">Sancte Marie in <placeName
                                ref="#places/4179">Ponposea</placeName></orgName>, cum consensu
                        domni <persName key="#Abbots" ref="#people/1599">Geronimi</persName> nostri
                            <rs key="#Abbots">abatis</rs> et cum consensu monachorum eiusdem
                        monasterii, michi presenti in Christi nomine <persName><name ref="Fuscardus"
                                >Fuscardo</name></persName> petitor pro me et pro iugale mea silicet
                                <persName><name ref="Inga">Inga</name></persName> seu filiis et
                        nepotibus nostris sub dominium et potestatem <rs key="#Priests"
                            >presbiteri</rs>
                        <persName key="#Priests"><name ref="Petrus">Petri</name></persName> fratris
                        tui, per <rs key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis">enfiteuticario iure</rs>
                        concessistis et largistis michi rem iuris predicti monasterii vestri, idest
                        omnes res et pertinentjas vestras quas usque modo posedit <persName
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis"><name ref="Petrus Sturianus">Petrus
                                Sturianus</name></persName> iure predicto monasterio que sunt posite
                        in fundo <geogName key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis #Fundi"
                            ref="#estates/3949"><placeName
                                key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis #Fundi"
                            >Meriaule</placeName></geogName>, cum ingresso et regresso suo et cum
                        omnibus suis pertinentjis, sitas <rs key="#Fines">territorio</rs>
                        <geogName key="#Fines" ref="#estates/3963"><placeName key="#Fines"
                                ref="#places/4830">Faventino acto
                            Corneliensis</placeName></geogName>, <rs key="#Plebs">plebe</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Fundi #Petiae #Plebs" ref="#juridical_persons/3627">Sancti
                            Iohannis in Libba</orgName>, <rs key="#Confinia">interraffines</rs> eius
                        hoc est: ab uno latere detinet eres quondam <persName key="#Confinia"><name
                                ref="Rusticus de Comperto">Rustici de Comperto</name></persName>, ab
                        alio latere <persName key="#Confinia"><name ref="Romaldus"
                            >Romaldus</name></persName> filius quondam <persName key="#Judge"><name
                                ref="Albertus">Alberti</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Judge">iudicis</rs>, a tertjo latere <persName key="#Confinia"
                                ><name ref="Wido">Uuido</name></persName> presbiteri <persName
                            key="#Priests"><name ref="Ursus">Ursonis</name></persName>, a quarto
                        latere vos predicti ordinatoris. Et insuper addidistis michi una <rs
                            key="#Petiae">petjola terre</rs> que est posita in fundo <geogName
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis #Fundi #Petiae" ref="#estates/3950"
                                ><placeName key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis #Fundi #Petiae"
                                >Maserie</placeName></geogName>, cum ingresso et regresso suo et cum
                        omnibus suis pertinentjis, constituta vero in predicto territorio et in
                        predicta plebe, interraffines eius idest: ab uno latere detinet <persName
                            key="#Confinia"><name ref="Romaldus">Romaldus</name></persName>, ab alio
                        latere <persName key="#Confinia"><name ref="Hugo">Ugo</name></persName>
                        <persName key="#Confinia"><name ref="Gherardus">Gerardi</name></persName>
                        filius, a tertjo iuris monasterii <orgName key="#Confinia"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/3641">Sancti Adalberti</orgName>, a quarto
                        latere <rs key="#Roads">via</rs> percurente. Hec omnia abendas, tenendas,
                        defensandas et in omnibus meliorandas, pensionis nomine singulis quibusque
                        anni omni martji mense infra ind(itjo)n(e) <rs key="#Rent_in_money">denariis
                            monete Venetje duodetjm</rs> tantum, pensio ut dictum est persolvatur.
                        Call(tjarii) nomine, idest <rs key="#Books">librum</rs> unum pro <rs
                            key="#Price">denariis monete Venetje libras tres</rs>. Si quis vero
                        partis nostre contra hanc aparam henfiteosin ire temtaverimus ante
                        perfinitum tempus sicut superius legitur det pars partis fidem servantis,
                        ante omne litis initjum aut interpell(atjonem), pene nomine, <rs
                            key="#Penalty">auri untjas duas</rs> et post penam solutam hec appara
                        henfiteosin maneat ratam. <persName key="#Tabellio"><name
                                ref="Wido Faventinus">Wido</name></persName> de Faven(tina) patria
                        Dei misericordia <rs key="#Tabellio">tabellio</rs> scribendum rogavi, sub
                        die et mense et ind(itjo)n(e) suprascripta quarta. Signum manus predicti
                        Fuscardi in ac appara a me facta subscripsi.</ab>
